prompts.common:
- inline inputs: existing_tags={{ input.existing_tags }}, protocol={{ input.protocol }}
- parameters: tag_note_language={{ parameter.tag_note_language }}

Execute the tasks strictly according to `SKILL.md`. Read `references/tag_standard.md` before generating tags. When Host Bridge is available, read the built-in `zotero-bridge-cli` wrapper skill and use `library-index get` with pagination to ground vocabulary design in the current Zotero library. If Host Bridge or the library index is unavailable, continue from the provided inputs and user interaction, and add a warning. Treat `add_tags` as objects similar to `tag-regulator.suggest_tags`: each item needs `tag` and `note`, with optional `facet`. Use `scripts/normalize_output.py` and `scripts/validate_output.py` when available before final stdout. Output exactly one valid JSON object to stdout.
